2. Install Claude Code
Anthropic now has a native installer â€” no Node.js path issues, no sudo problems.

Windows Installation
Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:
irm https://claude.ai/install.ps1 | iex

Then verify it worked:
claude --version
claude doctor

ğŸ’¡  If claude doctor shows PATH warnings
Run: echo $env:PATH in PowerShell and check that %USERPROFILE%\.local\bin appears. If not, restart your terminal after installation â€” the installer modifies your PATH but your current session hasn't reloaded it yet.

Authenticate
First time you run claude, it opens your browser to authenticate:
claude
Log in with your Claude.ai account. Done â€” credentials are saved permanently.

3. Set Up the RootByte Project

Step 1 â€” Create Your Project Folder
Choose where you want the project. Recommended: your Documents folder.
mkdir C:\Users\YourName\Documents\rootbyte
cd C:\Users\YourName\Documents\rootbyte

Step 2 â€” Copy the Project Files
Paste all the project files (index.html, CLAUDE.md, package.json, scripts/, src/) into this folder.
Your folder structure should look like this:
rootbyte/
  CLAUDE.md          â† Claude Code reads this first
  package.json
  .env.example       â† copy to .env and add your keys
  .gitignore
  src/
    index.html       â† the main website
    content/
      articles/      â† .md files, one per article
      trending.json  â† live trending data
  scripts/
    new-article.js
    fetch-trending.js

Step 3 â€” Set Up Environment Variables
Copy .env.example to .env and fill in your API keys:
copy .env.example .env
Open .env in WebStorm and fill in:
NEWS_API_KEY=your_key_from_newsapi.org
BREVO_API_KEY=your_key_from_brevo.com
ğŸ”‘  Where to get free API keys
NewsAPI.org: Sign up free â†’ 100 requests/day. Use for the trending section.
Brevo.com: Sign up free â†’ 300 emails/day. Use for the newsletter.

Step 4 â€” Open in WebStorm
Open WebStorm â†’ File â†’ Open â†’ select your rootbyte folder.
WebStorm will auto-detect the project structure. You should see the file tree on the left.

Step 5 â€” Set Up Git
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial RootByte project setup"

Then create a GitHub repo and push:
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/rootbyte.git
git push -u origin main

4. Configure WebStorm for Claude Code

Open the Built-in Terminal
WebStorm has a built-in terminal at the bottom. This is where you run Claude Code.
Keyboard shortcut: Alt + F12 (Windows) or use View â†’ Tool Windows â†’ Terminal.

Add Claude Code to External Tools (Optional but useful)
File â†’ Settings â†’ Tools â†’ External Tools â†’ Click + to add:
	â€¢	Name: Claude Code
	â€¢	Program: claude
	â€¢	Arguments: (leave blank)
	â€¢	Working directory: $ProjectFileDir$
Now you can launch Claude Code from the Tools menu directly inside WebStorm.

âš¡  Power Tip: Run Claude Code in the Terminal Panel
Keep WebStorm open with your files on the left, and Claude Code running in the bottom terminal panel. You can edit code manually AND ask Claude Code to make changes â€” both at the same time. Claude Code will see your changes in real time.

5. Daily Content Workflow
This is how you create and publish a new article. Takes 10-15 minutes once you have the routine.

In the WebStorm Terminal, start Claude Code:
claude

Tell Claude Code what to do:
Type in natural language â€” Claude Code reads your CLAUDE.md and knows the project:

What you say
What Claude Code does
"new article about the history of WiFi"
Creates scaffolded .md file, researches ROOT connection, fills in content
"fetch trending tech news"
Runs fetch-trending.js, updates trending.json, filters bad content
"update the tomorrow teaser to XRP article"
Edits index.html tomorrow box content directly
"add a new DYK card about the first hard drive"
Creates DYK JSON entry, updates the reel deck in TikTok mode
"deploy to Vercel"
Commits changes, pushes to GitHub, triggers Vercel auto-deploy


6. Deploy to Vercel (Free)

One-time Setup
	â€¢	Go to vercel.com and sign up with your GitHub account
	â€¢	Click "Add New Project" â†’ Import your rootbyte GitHub repo
	â€¢	Framework preset: Other (it's a static site)
	â€¢	Root directory: src
	â€¢	Click Deploy â€” Vercel will give you a URL like rootbyte.vercel.app
	â€¢	Add your custom domain in Settings â†’ Domains (optional)

Every Deploy After That
Just push to GitHub and Vercel deploys automatically:
git add .
git commit -m "New article: History of WiFi"
git push
Or tell Claude Code: "deploy to Vercel" and it does all three commands.

ğŸš€  Vercel Free Tier
Handles millions of requests per month for free. Your static HTML loads in under 200ms globally via Vercel's CDN. This speed directly affects your AdSense RPM â€” faster sites earn more per thousand pageviews.

